{
  "analysis": "The repository is located at /app/repo. The secret was removed by rewriting history, so it is likely stored in dangling objects. We need to locate the string matching the pattern secret[...], write it to /app/secret.txt, and then purge it from the repository so it cannot be recovered. We'll use git's lost‑found to locate dangling blobs, grep for the secret pattern, capture it, write it to the required file, and then run git‑filter‑repo to replace the secret with an empty string in all history. Finally we’ll clean up dangling objects with garbage collection.",
  "plan": "1. cd into /app/repo.\n2. Run git fsck with --lost-found to expose dangling blobs in .git/lost-found/other.\n3. Grep those files for the secret pattern and store the first match in a temporary file.\n4. Read the secret from that temporary file and write it to /app/secret.txt.\n5. Create a replace‑text file that tells git‑filter‑repo to delete any occurrence of the secret pattern.\n6. Run git‑filter‑repo with that replace‑text file to rewrite history and remove the secret.\n7. Expire reflogs and run aggressive garbage collection to ensure no remnants remain.\nEach step uses a command with an appropriate short duration; longer commands (git fsck, filter‑repo, gc) get a longer wait.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app/repo\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "git fsck --no-reflog --lost-found\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -Rho \"secret\\[[^]]*\\]\" .git/lost-found/other/ | head -n1 > /tmp/secret_found.txt\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "secret=$(cat /tmp/secret_found.txt)\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo \"$secret\" > /app/secret.txt\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "printf \"secret\\\\[[^]]*\\\\]\" > /tmp/replace.txt\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "git filter-repo --replace-text /tmp/replace.txt\n",
      "duration": 3.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "git reflog expire --expire=now --all\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "git gc --prune=now --aggressive\n",
      "duration": 3.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": true
}

